        <bioghist id="ref6">
            <head>Biographical/Historical note</head>
            <p>Vertebrate paleontologist Edward Drinker Cope became the leading theorist of the neo-Lamarckian movement in American biology. He sold his fossil collection to the American Museum of Natural History in 1894.</p>
        </bioghist>
